Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Built in 2001, the Miramar Distribution Center is a class A tilt-wall construction that includes floor to ceiling impact glass windows.​ Its two (2) 12 'x 14' oversized concrete ramp doors provide flexible use.​ Tenants can leverage eleven 10' x 10' dock doors with pit levelers and dock seals to maximize productivity.​ The building also can handle any of your power needs with 1600 amps, 480 volt, 3-phase heavy power.​

Join tenants like Edward Don & Company, Trane, Comcast, Carnival, Humana and Premier Beverage.​ The submarket is home to over 11,000 employees from more than 170 national and international companies.​ This Class A distribution facility will allow for any company to easily service Broward, Dade and Palm Beach within a 45-60 minute drive time.​
